File: Emergency paramedics wearing a full COVID-19 coronavirus personal protective equipment (PPE) transfer an empty gurney to an ambulance at the Greenacres Hospital in Port Elizabeth. JOHANNESBURG - The Health Department reported 29 more COVID-19 deaths, taking the death toll in South Africa to 16,938. Most of the new deaths occurred in Kwa-Zulu Natal. The total number of confirmed #COVID-19 cases is 679, 716. READ: COVID-19: Western Cape preparing for second wave The total number of recoveries is 612,763. SA has a COVID-19 recovery rate of 90%. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.